<subSubSection id="1A0F48190316A4DAF8ACECF8D1539D5D" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="3B88AFB9F8ADD72EFEEB53F8DD8E4918" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C52716FEF57F1CC6825FB5C71E29445F" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Recorded from southern Brazil and neighbouring Argentina growing in deciduous forest margins and scrub.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="46D4F11592E6FD15ADD1BE126486A022" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="22814D103BB38DCE00FEB5F7E40B9C1F" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">ARGENTINA. Misiones</emphasis>
: 
<normalizedToken id="646DC5F6A311AB2D5E9B6093B0A1D5B2" originalValue="Iguazú">Iguazu</normalizedToken>
, Wanda, 
<emphasis id="4D1C3DF8AB190117D05A81E41B2F6F3B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">H.A. Keller &amp; H.F. Romero</emphasis>
13252 (CTES, OXF); Montecarlo, Col. Guatambo, 
<emphasis id="C884365874410EB13844E1537DED2DDD" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">H.A. Keller</emphasis>
4038 (CTES).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6529D1B5BA4A3E3B12EE6EFB8AF0C59F" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="C54CB085BDB3ED175F966E220622DDEB" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">BRAZIL. Rio Grande do Sul</emphasis>
: 
<emphasis id="2EF73D83C95E068E10C3882E0C620D49" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P.P.A. Ferreira &amp; J. Durigon</emphasis>
705 (ICN, INPA); 
<normalizedToken id="45964EF61CEEA12C065BDAA9D7C8A473" originalValue="São">Sao</normalizedToken>
Francisco de Paula, 
<emphasis id="75266D9D56A7C930669F3B9295943B7C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">A. Seynam</emphasis>
10020 (MBM). 
<emphasis id="23C7CDBAF55BA0A3D1B6E3C2C35138BD" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Santa Catarina</emphasis>
: Descanso. 
<emphasis id="25787C11A16B0F4ED99EEFCB0BD78AA2" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">R.M. Klein</emphasis>
5119 (HBR) fide Ferreira et al. (2013: 32).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4D2AFCF7B5B3DF93AA5613ABEA1B2F8D" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="8922352C9838588EBA6BFEA23D0CA1A2" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Notes</emphasis>
. This species is distinguished by its small outer sepal and very lax, branched inflorescence and glabrous corolla.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="07F1362791A7FE84732166F7E961B2AE" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">The placement of this species is uncertain.</paragraph>
